Detailed Description

Structure of linkaggregation group

The naming rules on Ethernet linkaggregation are as follows:


1. name="EMS";value="CompanyName/EMSname"

2. name="ManagedElement";value="ManagedElementName"

3. name="LAG";value="xx"

globaldefs::NamingAttributes_T name:
The name of the linkaggregation. This name must be unique networkwide and do not change with EMS upgrade.

string nativeEMSName:
The local name of the linkaggregation object. It is also the character string showed on T2000 interfaces.

string userLabel:
The user label of the linkaggregation object. It is also the character string showed on NMS interfaces.

string owner:
The owner of the linkaggregation object.

globaldefs::NVSList_T paraList:
Parameters of the linkaggregation, including the LAG type(MANUAL,STATIC),sharing type(SHARE,NOSHARE).

globaldefs::NamingAttributes_T mainport:
The main port of the linkaggregation.

HW_LAGBranchPortList_T branchPortList:
The branchport list.

globaldefs::NVSList_T additionalInfo:
This attribute allows the communication from the EMS to the NMS of additional information which isn't explicitly modelled. It is a readonly attribute.
